Thank you @ladyjoe_ for having me as your guest on #ConfessionsGourmandes. I very much enjoyed our tête-a-tête. It’s always grounding to reconnect with my French side, speak about my upbringing in Lyon, and life as a chef in New York City. I look forward to cooking for you soon!  

Merci @ladyjoe_ pour ce moment de conversation transatlantique, votre passion pour les chefs et leur cuisine et votre affection pour New York. Je vous attends a @restaurantdaniel et @lepavillonnyc pour vous faire découvrir notre cuisine.

A few months ago, I also had the opportunity to present the @franciebrooklyn team their very first #MichelinStar over a surprise interview with @chefcipollone and @johnwinterman , a close friend and #RestaurantDANIEL alum. Congratulations to both you and your team!

#Repost @michelinguide with
・・・
Congratulations to @franciebrooklyn on its MICHELIN Star. Chef-owner Christopher Cipollone chatted with Two Star Daniel chef-owner @danielboulud about Francie's modern brasserie vibes. 

Our Inspectors say, "Cipollone excels at balancing intriguing flavors and textures and his expertise on is on display in contemporary pasta dishes, his signature pithivier and the sauces that accompany each course.

Thanks to our partner @remymartinus! #remymartin

See the entire MICHELIN Guide New York selection for 2021 at https://bit.ly/3tL6PYT
and stay tuned for more of the 2021 MICHELIN Guide announcements.
.
.
.
#MICHELINguideNY #MICHELINSTAR21 #OneMICHELINStar#restaurant #chef #gastronomy #AllinNYC

Join me for a series of virtual cooking classes, beginning this Thursday (1/14) at 6pm EST, featuring some of my favorite French classics. For every class purchased, we are donating one meal to @citymeals, a charity near and dear to my heart that provides nourishing meals to homebound elderly New Yorkers. Today, with the support of @food1stfoundation, we produce 1,200 meals a day. Visit the EVENT CALENDAR on DANIELBOULUD.COM to purchase your class. I look forward to cooking with all of you! Learn more about
@danielbouludkitchen @restaurantdaniel

node.text: This morning we had the pleasure to welcome @beardfoundation CEO @clarereichenbach and Director of Programming @jbfizabela at @restaurantdaniel to congratulate the new Beard House Fellow recipient @mimichen121. Upon graduating from the @iccedu, Mimi returned to us as an extern at #DANIEL, where she continued to grow as a cook. In 2017, she placed first in the @Mentorbkb Commis Competition, giving her the opportunity to stage with #TeamUSA 2017 and join them in my hometown #Lyon for the @bocusedor, the most challenging gastronomic competition in the world. I am so proud of your accomplishments Mimi, will always be there to give you advice, and look forward to your future endeavors.
